# File & Module Conventions

## One util per file, named after the function
`formatPrice.ts` exports `formatPrice`; `getMinimumOrder.ts` exports
`getMinimumOrder`. Filenames are camelCase (utils/hooks) or PascalCase
(components/classes).

## No barrel files
Never create re-export-only `index.ts`. Import directly from the defining
module. `@comfort-b2b/shared` exposes explicit `package.json` `exports`
subpaths (e.g. `@comfort-b2b/shared/constants`), so import:

```ts
import { MIN_ORDER } from "@comfort-b2b/shared/constants";
```

When adding a new shared module, add a matching `exports` subpath entry.

## Co-located tests
Put `foo.test.ts` next to `foo.ts`. Import test globals explicitly:

```ts
import { describe, expect, it } from "@jest/globals";
```

## Import order (lint-enforced)
Groups `[builtin, external, internal, parent, sibling, index]`, a blank line
between groups, alphabetized. `@comfort-b2b/*` and `@/*` count as internal.

## DRY
Extract reusable helpers/hooks/components instead of copy/pasting logic.
